svg.text: Assignment​•You will be designing budgets for three families, each ​with 4 people (2 parents and 2 kids)​o​One family lives below the poverty line, with an ​annual income of less than $22,350​​(Department of Health and Human Services)​o​The other family is an average Massachusetts ​household with 2 parents and one kid, with an ​annual income of $64,509​​(2006-2010 Census data).​o​The last family is a member of the top 1% with an ​income of $506,553​​(New York Times).
